CNet 5 SDK - License and Attribution
=====================================

This repository contains two categories of material with different terms:

1. Original CNet SDK materials (headers, FD files, examples, reference docs)
2. New work (GCC porting code, documentation, build system, tools, tests)


ORIGINAL CNET SDK MATERIALS
----------------------------

The original CNet 5 SDK was distributed as part of cnet5demo.lha on Aminet
(the public Amiga software archive). The SDK contains dual copyright notices:

  - Some files are marked "copyright ZenMetal Software"
  - Some files (notably examples) are marked:
    "copyright 1998 Ray A. Akey / Exclusive license granted to
     ZenMetal Software and CNet door coders"

The "CNet door coders" grant explicitly covers the SDK's target audience:
developers writing doors, PFiles, and utilities for CNet BBS systems. The
distribution of the demo package on Aminet (a public archive) implies
permission for use by BBS operators and door developers.

Original authors and rights holders:

  - Ken Pletzer             - CNet BBS original creator (Perspective Software)
  - Ray Akey                - Primary developer, v4.x and v5.x (ZenMetal Software)
  - Todd Knight             - ZenMetal Software co-founder
  - Kelly Cochran           - cnetc.library and SDK contributor
  - Dan FitzGerald          - Current CNet maintainer
  - Perspective Software    - Original CNet publisher
  - ZenMetal Software       - CNet publisher (v4.x and v5.x era)

These original materials are redistributed here under their original terms.
No additional restrictions are imposed by this project.

CNet BBS binaries (cnet.library, cnetc.library, cnet4.library,
cnetmail.library, cnetgui.library, and the Control/bbs executables) are NOT
included in this repository. They must be obtained separately from the
cnet5demo.lha distribution on Aminet or an existing CNet installation.


